oai_dc:dc.dc:title: The Quality-Minded Dairy Practitioner
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Fuhrmann, Thomas
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: quality service
veterinary practice
dairy practitioner
preventive medicine
individual cow
emergency services
production medicine
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The concept of providing quality service to dairy clients has always been a hallmark of the veterinary profession. Whether your practice provides primarily individual cow and emergency services, or whether your primary aim is preventive medicine, or if you involve yourself in production medicine, dairy practitioners try to provide quality service that best fits client needs.
